# FILE MANIFEST — Every file to add to the repository
_All files live inside the `events_app/` folder of your repo, at the exact
paths shown. The zip (events_app_champagne_revA.zip) contains all of them
already in the right folder structure — unzip it into `events_app/` and
you're done. This manifest is the labeled index._

---

## FRONT END — what the user sees and touches

**F1 · App Entry & Shell**
`lib/main.dart` — Starts the app, wires the theme and database together, opens the Events Hub.

**F2 · Champagne Rev A Design System**
`lib/theme/champagne_theme.dart` — Every color, font (Prata/Jost), corner radius, and animation timing for the whole app. The only file where style values are allowed to exist.

**F3 · Events Hub Screen**
`lib/screens/home_screen.dart` — The home screen: list of event cards, the "Every celebration starts here" empty state, and the Create event button.

**F4 · Create & Edit Event Screen**
`lib/screens/event_create_screen.dart` — The four-step flow (type → tradition → name → date/venue). Only the name is required. Doubles as the edit screen.

**F5 · Event Dashboard Screen**
`lib/screens/event_dashboard_screen.dart` — Opens when you tap an event: masthead on top, six "coming soon" module cards, edit and delete buttons. Delete asks "Delete Sofía & Miguel? This can't be undone."

**F6 · Event Masthead (signature component)**
`lib/widgets/event_masthead.dart` — The invitation-style header: name in Prata with the gold "&", uppercase letterspaced date · venue, satin gold progress bar, status line.

**F7 · Module Card**
`lib/widgets/module_card.dart` — The small dashboard tiles (Checklist, Budget, Guests, Seating, Templates, Run of show).

**F8 · App Text (strings map)**
`lib/strings/app_strings.dart` — Every word the user reads, in one file, ready for Spanish translation in v1.x (D-003).

---

## BACK END — where the data lives (on the user's device)

**B1 · Database Definition**
`lib/data/app_database.dart` — The drift/SQLite database: the events table and how it opens on each platform (phone, desktop, web demo).

**B2 · Generated Database Helper**
`lib/data/app_database.g.dart` — ⚠️ You don't write this one. It's created on your machine by running `dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs` (SETUP.md step 4). Commit it once generated.

**B3 · Event Repository**
`lib/data/event_repository.dart` — The middleman: screens ask it to create, read, update, delete, and watch events. Screens never touch the database directly.

**B4 · Event Model**
`lib/models/event.dart` — The shape of an event (name, type, tradition, date, venue, guest goal, linked events) per SCHEMA.md.

---

## TESTS — proof the app works

**T1 · Model Tests**
`test/event_model_test.dart` — Checks the event object copies, clears, and serializes correctly.

**T2 · Database & Persistence Tests**
`test/event_repository_test.dart` — Proves create → edit → delete works and data survives restart (acceptance criterion 2).

**T3 · Create-Flow Test**
`test/create_flow_widget_test.dart` — Walks the create flow like a user would and asserts the empty-state copy and the name-required rule.

---

## PROJECT & DOCS — repo housekeeping

**P1 · Dependencies**
`pubspec.yaml` — The package list (drift, google_fonts, intl, uuid). Replaces the existing one in events_app/.

**P2 · Setup Guide**
`SETUP.md` — Beginner walkthrough: copy files, install packages, generate B2, run checks, run the app. Place at `events_app/SETUP.md` (or repo root).

**P3 · Corrected README** *(delivered earlier)*
`README.md` — Repo root. Storage = drift, website = free demo, style-tile warning.

**P4 · Decisions Log Additions** *(delivered earlier)*
`DECISIONS-additions.md` — Append entries D-016, D-017, D-018 to your existing DECISIONS.log, then delete this helper file.

**P5 · Brief Amendment** *(delivered earlier)*
`BRIEF-001-amendment-A.md` — Repo root, next to BRIEF-001, so any builder reads both.

